          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              Not that I ever heard anything like that from a little kid, but I'd say that science got us to the moon, made us fly, made really big explosions possible, got us icecream shops, bikes, rollerskates, gaming consoles...<BR><BR>I'd more expect to find that attitude in teenagers with boring science teachers, and they wouldn't be objecting to science as such, they'd just find it increadibly dull. The answer then would be to get them a good science teacher.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
