        <tr>
          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              The Space Race between the USSR and the US would be a great STS* topic.  You've got the politics of the Cold War that made becoming a scientist practically a patriotic duty.  You've got the engineering search for the perfect nozzle shape and rocket configuration.  You've got the technological challenge of creating a "bio-zone" in the vacuum of space.  You've got the actualy physics and chemistry of the rocket and its fuel.<BR><BR>It just may be that a middle school or high school student might be totally captured by an interdisciplinary approach such as an STS examination of the Space Race.<BR><BR><small>*Science, Technology and Society or Science and Technology Studies</small>

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
